history.content:
{
  "narration": "The ancient Lost Ward Circle stands before you, its seven weathered monoliths casting long shadows under the flickering glow of the dying blue ward energy. As you step into the clearing's barren earth, the air grows heavy with an unsettling chill. Suddenly, from the mists between the stones, two spectral figures materialize, their ghostly forms swirling with malice and piercing you with cold, empty eyes. Above the center dais, a will-o'-wisp hovers, its eerie light pulsing like a heartbeat of predatory intent. The ward's protective magic may be fading, but these ethereal guardians are vigilant and deadly. The initiative order is established: the second specter strikes swiftly at 14, followed closely by the first specter at 13, then the will-o'-wisp glowing at 8, with you, Norn, moving last at 1. The battle for the fate of the Lost Ward Circle is about to begin. Prepare yourself and tell me, what is your first move? When you are ready to attack, roll a d20 and add your attack bonus.",
  "actions": []
}

{
  "narration": "The second specter moves first, its ghostly form swirling as it lunges at you with a chilling life drain attack. It rolls a d20... a 20! That's a critical hit! Rolling damage, doubling damage dice for the critical strike: it rolls 3d6 and 3d6 for the necrotic life drain, getting 2, 7, 3 plus 2, 7, 3, total 24 necrotic damage! The cold drains into your very soul, sapping your vitality. You feel your strength falter as the specter attempts to steal your life energy.\n\nNext, the first specter attacks. It rolls a d20... an 11. Adding its attack bonus +4, total 15. Your armor class is 16, so the attack misses as you deftly evade the creeping grasp.\n\nThe will-o'-wisp flickers erratically, then shoots a bolt of lightning at you. Rolling a d20... 19! Adding the attack bonus +4, total 23, a hit! It rolls damage: 2d8 lightning damage, results 2 and 7, totaling 9 damage searing your flesh with arcs of crackling energy.\n\nNow, Norn, it's your turn. You have taken 33 points of damage from the specter's critical life drain and the will-o'-wisp's lightning shock, but you remain standing. The second specter stares with soulless eyes, ready to strike again. Please roll a d20 for your attack roll and add your attack bonus of +5. Let me know the result when ready.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Norn takes 24 necrotic damage from the second specter's critical life drain attack and 9 lightning damage from the will-o'-wisp's shock, total 33 damage. Current HP: 29 - 33 = -4, Norn is unconscious."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "The second specter strikes first, its ghostly claws reaching out with a chilling touch. It rolls a d20... a natural 20! With your Improved Critical feature, this is a devastating critical hit. Rolling damage for the life drain attack twice over: 2, 7, 3 and again 2, 7, 3 totals 24 necrotic damage. The coldness unnerves you as your life's energy bleeds away, reducing your hit points from 29 down to 5. The first specter follows swiftly, but its attack roll of 11 plus 4 equals 15, just shy of your armor class of 16, missing its mark.\n\nSuddenly the will-o'-wisp darts forward, unleashing a searing shock of lightning. The attack roll is 19 plus 4, totaling 23, striking true. It deals 9 lightning damage, dragging your HP down from 5 to -4. You collapse to the ground, the dark energy overwhelming your body as you slip unconscious.\n\nYour vision fades as the malevolent energies of the Lost Ward Circle press in. You will need to make death saving throws on your turns to cling to life.\n\nThe round ends with your allies yet to act and enemies ready to continue their assault.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Norn takes 24 necrotic damage from the second specter's critical life drain and 9 lightning damage from the will-o'-wisp's shock, reducing HP from 29 to -4. Norn is now unconscious."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Each specter has one action per turn, and that usually means they make one attack with their Life Drain ability. They will use this attack once during their turn, attempting to weaken their foes by draining their life force. If you want, I can continue narrating the second round of actions now, or answer any other questions you have about the combat.",
  "actions": []
}

{
  "narration": "Understood, Norn. I will update your hit points to 11 to reflect the total damage taken, considering 9 from the specter's life drain and 9 from the will-o'-wisp's lightning. You're still conscious and ready to act in this critical moment. Your turn has arrived. What will you do? Remember to roll a d20 for your attack roll and add your attack bonus of +5.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Norn's hit points set to 11 to correctly reflect damage from specter and will-o'-wisp attacks."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "I have updated your hit points to 11 to correctly reflect the damage you sustained from the specter and will-o'-wisp. Your condition is now 'none', meaning you are conscious and ready to continue the fight. The specters and will-o'-wisp watch you carefully, waiting for your next move. What will you do? When ready, please roll a d20 for your attack and add your attack bonus of +5.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Norn's hit points set to 11. Condition set to none, indicating Norn is conscious and able to act."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Your hit points are now accurately set to 11, reflecting the damage absorbed from the specter and the will-o'-wisp's attacks. Your status remains 'alive' as you are conscious and fighting, with no harmful conditions currently affecting you. The specters and the eerie light of the will-o'-wisp intensify as they watch your next move closely. What will be your action? When ready, please roll a d20 for your attack roll and add your attack bonus of +5.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Norn's hit points set to 11. Status remains 'alive'. Conditions set to none."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You reach deep within yourself, summoning your Fighter's resilience through your Second Wind ability. You regain hit points equal to 1d10 plus your fighter level, which is 4. Please roll a d10 and tell me the result so I can calculate your healing total.",
  "actions": []
}

{
  "narration": "You focus your breath and spirit, channeling your fighter's hardy resolve to heal yourself. With the 9 you rolled on the d10 plus your fighter level of 4, you regain 13 hit points, raising your current hit points from 11 to 24. This surge of renewed vitality steadies your resolve amidst the spectral foes surrounding you. Now, with a clearer head, you can strike back. What is your next action? Remember to roll a d20 and add your attack bonus of +5 if you choose to attack.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Norn uses Second Wind to regain 13 hit points. Current HP: 11 + 13 = 24."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You summon your inner strength and call upon your Second Wind. Your body rebounds with raw resilience as you regain 13 hit points, fully restoring you from 29 up to your maximum of 36 hit points. Feeling reinvigorated, you stand ready to face the looming specters and the will-o'-wisp. What will be your next move? When you are ready to attack, roll a d20 and add your attack bonus of +5.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Norn uses Second Wind to regain 13 hit points. Current HP: 29 + 13 = 36 (max HP)."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Thank you for clarifying, Norn. Your hit points are correctly updated to 24 after using Second Wind from your previous 11 hit points. Now, you step forward to strike the first specter with a fearsome critical hit! Your first attack roll is a 19, which hits and triggers your Improved Critical feature, confirming a critical hit. For your damage, you will roll your weapon's damage dice twice and add your Strength modifier once. After this, using your Action Surge, you make a second attack roll of 18, which also hits. Roll your damage dice normally for the second attack and add your Strength modifier once. Please roll the damage dice for both attacks or tell me if you'd like me to roll them for you.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Norn's hit points set to 24 after Second Wind from 11 HP."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "With precision and strength, your first critical hit cleaves into the first specter, dealing 18 points of slashing damage. The spectral creature flickers but remains. You follow up quickly with your action surge, landing a second strike for 6 damage. The combined total of 24 damage severely injures the first specter, its form wavering dangerously. The battle rages on. The two specters and the will-o'-wisp still loom, as they prepare their next moves.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "B04-E1",
        "changes": "First specter loses 24 hit points from Norn's attacks. Current HP: 22 - 24 = -2, changing status to 'dead'."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Your first critical hit cleaves through the first specter, and with your follow-up strike granted by your Action Surge, the spectral form is torn apart, dissipating into nothingness. The specter is destroyed and will no longer threaten you. The remaining specter and will-o'-wisp hiss and pulse with malevolent energy as they prepare to continue the fight.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "B04-E1",
        "changes": "First specter loses 24 hit points from Norn's attacks and is reduced from 22 to -2 HP. Status changed to 'dead'."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Your first critical hit cleaves through the first specter, and with your follow-up strike granted by your Action Surge, the spectral form is torn apart, dissipating into nothingness. The specter is destroyed and will no longer threaten you. The remaining specter and will-o'-wisp hiss and pulse with malevolent energy as they prepare to continue the fight.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "B04-E1",
        "changes": "First specter loses 24 hit points from Norn's attacks and is reduced from 22 to -2 HP. Status changed to 'dead'."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "The undead close in to strike back. The second specter lashes out with its life drain attack. It rolls a d20... a 17, adding +4 for a total of 21, hitting your armor class of 16. Rolling damage: 3d6 necrotic damage, result 2, 3, 4, totaling 9 damage. The chill drains your vitality, reducing your hit points from 24 to 15. The will-o'-wisp pulses next, firing a shock of lightning with a d20 roll of 10 plus 4 attack bonus to get 14, which misses your armor class. The battle rages fiercely. The first specter is gone, but the second specter and will-o'-wisp remain. Your turn, Norn. Please roll a d20 for your attack roll and add your attack bonus of +5.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Norn takes 9 necrotic damage from the second specter's life drain attack, reducing HP from 24 to 15."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You lunge forward, your blade slicing through the spectral form with precision. Your attack roll is a 19, which hits the remaining specter's armor class of 12 with ease. You then deal 17 points of slashing damage with your strike. The specter wails as it takes the blow, its form flickering violently before collapsing into vapors and dissipating into the air. The spectral guardian is destroyed and no longer a threat.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "B04-E1",
        "changes": "Second specter loses 17 hit points from Norn's attack, reducing its HP from 22 to 5."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You lunge forward, your blade slicing through the spectral form with precision. Your attack roll is a 19, which hits the remaining specter's armor class of 12 with ease. You deal 17 points of slashing damage, leaving the specter grievously wounded but still lingering with 5 hit points. The twisted spirit snarls in pain, its form flickering but not yet vanishing. It remains a threat, albeit on the brink of collapse.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "B04-E1",
        "changes": "Second specter loses 17 hit points from Norn's attack, reducing its HP from 22 to 5."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "The remaining specter, still wounded but persistent, lashes out with a despairing fury. It rolls a d20 for its attack... a 19! Adding its +4 attack bonus, the total is 23, hitting your armor class of 16. Now it rolls damage, 3d6 necrotic: 2, 2, 5, totaling 9 necrotic damage. The cold life drain chills you to the bone, reducing your hit points from 15 to 6. Meanwhile, the will-o'-wisp flashes with eerie light and fires a jolt of electricity. It rolls a d20... an 18 plus 4 is 22, hitting your AC. Rolling damage: 2d8 lightning damage, 4 and 3, totaling 7 damage. You stagger slightly from the shock, reducing your HP from 6 to -1 and falling unconscious.\n\nYour condition is now unconscious, and you begin to make death saving throws on your turn. The battle is turning dire.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Norn takes 16 damage: 9 necrotic from specter's life drain, 7 lightning from will-o'-wisp's shock. HP reduced from 15 to -1. Norn falls unconscious."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "When a player character drops to 0 hit points or below and becomes unconscious, they fall prone and are unable to take any actions or reactions. During subsequent turns, the player must make death saving throws at the start of their turn to determine if they stabilize or succumb. You roll a d20 without any modifiers: a roll of 10 or higher counts as a success; below 10 is a failure. Three successes mean you stabilize and stop making death saves, remaining unconscious but no longer dying. Three failures result in death. Any natural 20 on a death saving throw allows you to regain 1 hit point and regain consciousness immediately. If you take any damage while unconscious, you automatically fail a death saving throw, or take two failures if the damage is a critical hit. You can be stabilized by receiving healing from an ally, but until then, you must rely on these death saves. Your next turn, you will make the first death saving throw. I will guide you through this when your turn comes.",
  "actions": []
}

{
  "narration": "Monsters generally recognize unconscious characters as easy targets, but their specific behaviors can vary based on their intelligence, instincts, and motivations. In this encounter, the specters and the will-o'-wisp will continue their attacks during their turns, typically targeting the closest or most threatening opponent. Since you are unconscious, the monsters may shift their focus to other threats if present, but if you remain engaged and within reach, they may attempt to finish you off. However, some monsters don't distinguish and simply attack the nearest character they perceive as a threat, regardless of their state. The specters are malevolent spirits intent on draining life, so they might target you to ensure your demise while the will-o'-wisp could try to harass or distract. Be wary — your unconscious state leaves you vulnerable until allies can aid you or you can stabilize yourself.",
  "actions": []
}

{
  "narration": "Understood. I will restore 20 hit points to Norn and clear any conditions so that you can continue the fight unimpeded. Norn's hit points increase from -1 to 19, and the condition is set to none. You are back in the fight, ready to face down the remaining specter and will-o'-wisp.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Norn regains 20 hit points, increasing from -1 to 19. Conditions cleared to none, status remains alive."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Norn's vitality surges back forthwith as 20 hit points are restored, bringing you from -1 to a healthy 19 HP. All conditions are cleared, and your status is now alive and fully ready to continue the battle against the lingering threats of the specter and will-o'-wisp. Your companions watch closely, hopeful as you prepare your next move. What will you do?",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Norn's hit points have been restored from -1 to 19. Status set to 'alive'. Conditions cleared."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Norn's vitality returns as 20 hit points are restored, healing him from -1 to 19 hit points. His status is now set to 'alive' and all conditions have been cleared, putting him back in fighting shape. The specter and will-o'-wisp maintain their menacing presence, but you are ready to continue the battle with renewed vigor. What is your next action?",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Norn's hit points restored from -1 to 19. Status set to 'alive'. Conditions cleared."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You aim a precise strike at the remaining specter, your attack roll totals 15, enough to hit its armor class of 12. Rolling your damage dice, you deal 10 points of damage to the specter. The ghostly form shudders and flickers under the blow but clings stubbornly to existence with 5 hit points remaining, still a dangerous foe.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "B04-E1",
        "changes": "Second specter takes 10 damage from Norn's attack. HP reduced from 5 to -5, changing status to 'dead'."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Your strike lands true against the last remaining specter. With an attack roll of 15, you cut through its ethereal form dealing 10 damage. The wounded specter's form trembles violently before dissipating into nothingness, effectively destroyed by your blow. The threat of the specters is finally ended, leaving only the will-o'-wisp hovering ominously above the ritual dais.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "B04-E1",
        "changes": "Second specter takes 10 damage from Norn's attack. HP reduced from 5 to -5, status changed to 'dead'."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Your strike lands true against the last remaining specter. With an attack roll of 15, you cut through its ethereal form dealing 10 damage. The wounded specter's form trembles violently before dissipating into nothingness, effectively destroyed by your blow. The threat of the specters is finally ended, leaving only the will-o'-wisp hovering ominously above the ritual dais.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "B04-E1",
        "changes": "Second specter takes 10 damage from Norn's attack, reducing HP from 5 to -5 and changing status to 'dead'."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "With the two specters defeated, only the glowing will-o'-wisp remains, its eerie light flickering with malicious intent above the ritual dais. The air crackles with arcane energy as the creature circles silently, preparing to strike. Norn, standing firm and ready, you prepare to face this last threat. What will your next move be? When ready, roll a d20 and add your attack bonus of +5 to see if your strike connects.",
  "actions": []
}

{
  "narration": "You steady your aim and strike at the will-o'-wisp, rolling a d20 and getting a 19, a solid hit against its AC of 19! For damage, you roll a total of 16 points. The radiant shock from your strike sears through the will-o'-wisp's ethereal form, causing it to flicker and wail in pain. The creature now has 6 hit points remaining, clearly weakened but still dangerous.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "B04-E1",
        "changes": "Will-o'-wisp takes 16 points of damage from Norn's attack, reducing its hit points from 22 to 6."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Indeed, the will-o'-wisp, angered by your assault, prepares to retaliate. It zips through the air with agility, its flickering light focused on you. It makes an attack roll... rolling a d20, it results in a 20! A natural hit! The will-o'-wisp's shock attack surges forward, crackling with deadly energy. Rolling damage now: 2d8 lightning damage results in 6 and 5, totaling 11 points. The electric surge arcs through you, leaving a sizzling sensation as it drains your vitality. Your current hit points are reduced accordingly. Stay strong, Norn. The fight continues.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Norn takes 11 lightning damage from the will-o'-wisp's shock attack. Current HP reduced from 19 to 8."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You swing your weapon decisively against the will-o'-wisp, your attack roll of 17 surpassing its armor class of 19 narrowly, hitting despite its elusive nature. You deal 7 points of damage, your blow hitting the flickering form and causing it to wail with pain. The will-o'-wisp's hit points drop from 6 to -1 as it dissipates into a faint spark and vanishes, defeated at last. The Lost Ward Circle falls silent, the dangerous spirits banished for now.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "B04-E1",
        "changes": "Will-o'-wisp takes 7 damage from Norn's attack, reducing HP from 6 to -1, status changed to 'dead'."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "exit",
      "parameters": {}
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You strike at the will-o'-wisp with a focused blow, but your attack roll of 17 falls short of its armor class of 19. Your strike misses, leaving the will-o'-wisp unscathed and still hovering menacingly at 6 hit points. The creature flickers brightly, preparing to retaliate as the battle continues.",
  "actions": []
}

{
  "narration": "Thanks for clarifying, Norn. With your attack roll of 17 plus your +5 attack bonus, your total is 22, which exceeds the will-o'-wisp's armor class of 19. Your attack hits! You deal 7 points of damage as you strike the flickering will-o'-wisp, reducing its hit points from 6 to -1. The creature's light dims and fades as it dissipates into nothingness, defeated at last. The Lost Ward Circle is now free of the undead threat. Congratulations on your hard-fought victory!",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "B04-E1",
        "changes": "Will-o'-wisp takes 7 damage from Norn's attack, HP reduced from 6 to -1, status set to 'dead'."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "exit",
      "parameters": {}
    }
  ]
}

Combat Summary: {
  "narration": "After a fierce battle at the Lost Ward Circle, Norn has emerged victorious, having defeated two malevolent specters and a cunning will-o'-wisp. Your final strike dispersed the last undead menace as its light faded into nothingness, leaving the ancient stones in eerie silence once more. This hard-fought triumph grants you 850 experience points, reflecting the challenge of overcoming these spectral guardians in their haunted domain. Your steadfast courage and skill have preserved the fragile magic of the ward circle, at least for now.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "B04-E1",
        "changes": "Both specters are dead with hit points at -2 and -5, and the will-o'-wisp is dead with hit points at -1."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Norn gains 850 experience points for defeating three enemies in the Lost Ward Circle encounter."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "exit",
      "parameters": {}
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Within the decrepit walls of the Abandoned Ranger Outpost, you notice the eerie silence is broken by the faint, rustling skittering from above and around you. Two swarms of tiny spiders, their multitude of legs tapping lightly against the broken beams, emerge from the shadows, their hunger apparent. From the rafters, a large giant spider, its eyes glinting malevolently in the dim light, prepares to drop down on its unsuspecting prey. The air is thick with tension and the promise of a fierce battle. The initiative order is set: the swarm of spiders will act first, followed immediately by you, Norn, and finally, the giant spider lurking overhead. The swarms shift restlessly, ready to strike. Brace yourself, fighter, and prepare your first move. What will your opening action be? Remember to roll your d20 and add your attack bonus or make any other roll necessary.",
  "actions": []
}

{
  "narration": "The ancient wooden beams creak ominously as you stand within the Abandoned Ranger Outpost. Shadows writhe along the walls, and from the dark corners, a swarm of spiders stirs, sensing your presence. Suddenly, the swarm surges forward to attack first. Its tiny legs crawl rapidly over the floor as it lunges at you with a flurry of bites. The swarm rolls a d20 for its attack, landing a 14 on the die, plus 3 for its attack bonus, to total 17—enough to strike your armor. It then rolls damage, resulting in 7 piercing damage from its multiple tiny bites. You feel sharp stings across your skin as the swarm's attack lands. The swarm recoils but remains poised to strike again later. Now, it is your turn, Norn. The giant spider above watches from the rafters, ready to pounce once the opportunity arises. You steady your stance. What will you do? Remember to roll your d20 and add your attack modifier for your action.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Norn takes 7 points of piercing damage from the Swarm of Spiders' attack. Current HP: 26 - 7 = 19."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You carefully assess the dim interior of the outpost. You see the giant spider lurking high in the rafters, its multiple eyes glinting as it prepares to drop down on its prey. On the floor, a single swarm of tiny spiders scurries and shifts, ready to attack at a moment's notice. So, you face one giant spider and one swarm of spiders here. What is your next move, Norn? Remember, you act after the swarm's turn and before the giant spider's.",
  "actions": []
}

{
  "narration": "You raise your longsword and strike decisively at the swarm of spiders. Your roll of 19 scores a critical hit, making your attack even deadlier. You deal your damage: rolling 8 and 7 on the damage dice, adding your +3 bonus for a total of 18 points of slashing damage. The swarm convulses under the sharp strike but remains alive, hanging on by a thread. Using your fighter's Action Surge, you then swiftly retreat toward the door, positioning yourself at a narrow entrance to block the giant spider's advance. The giant spider above snarls in frustration as you put this natural bottleneck between it and yourself. The swarm now teeters on the edge of destruction, wounded severely but still potentially dangerous. The giant spider prepares to act next.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "B02-E1",
        "changes": "Swarm of Spiders loses 18 hit points from Norn's critical hit longsword attack. Current HP: 22 - 18 = 4."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You brace yourself behind the narrow doorway, using the structure to your advantage as the giant spider shifts its weight in the rafters above. It snarls, preparing to leap down and strike you through the confined space. It lunges forward with its bite, rolling a 11 plus 5 for a total of 16 against your armor class of 16. The attack just manages to hit! You feel the spider's bite piercing your armor as it sinks its fangs in. For damage, it rolls 7 on the d8 plus 3 for a total of 10 piercing damage. The sting leaves you reeling slightly, but you maintain your stance. The battle continues, with you buffered by the doorway, and the swarm of spiders still dangling on the edge of collapse.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Norn takes 10 points of piercing damage from the giant spider's bite. Current HP: 26 - 10 = 16."
      }
    }
  ]
